    "setting": "A regional water authority monitoring a 40-mile river corridor\nwith 6 sensor stations (WQ-01 through WQ-06, upstream to\ndownstream). Daily reports include: pH, dissolved oxygen (DO),\nturbidity (NTU), temperature, conductivity, and heavy metals\npanel (chromium Cr, lead Pb, cadmium Cd, mercury Hg, arsenic As)\nat each station. Field inspector notes from weekly site visits.\nCompliance flags against EPA MCL thresholds. An unpermitted\nindustrial discharge between stations WQ-02 and WQ-03 is\nreleasing hexavalent chromium. The concentration gradient\nacross stations reveals the point source location.\n",
    "voice": "Technical measurement data with units. Terse field inspector\nnotes. Regulatory compliance language. Station-by-station\ntabular readings. No interpretive commentary \u2014 measurements,\nflags, and short field observations only.\n"
  },
